To Angela - I have very poor reception and have gotten discouraged more than
once to say the least.  I have asked them for advice and I clearly received
a message that stated I should meditate to help my connection.  When I do
take the time to meditate before a session it does seem to be a better
signal.  I even asked them right after I meditate if it helped and they
responded that yes indeed it helped.  Of course I am horrible at meditating
and I haven&#39;t taken to the process very well :-)  I&#39;ll post my clips of them
telling me to mediate.  Look in Kristin&#39;s File.

I hope that helps you.

Charm - Sorry you had such trouble with your neighbors.  But I just want to
say that I am saddened for your loss of Monique. It is like a death no doubt
about it and you will miss her always.  Hopefully she will be able to visit
you wherever you are and maybe you will hear from her again.  I know how
much you enjoyed having her around.  And your feelings are natural so don&#39;t
feel bad about that.  Take care and I look forward to when you are full
throttle again!

k

  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Pridegrl Neverumind
Sent: Thursday, June 26, 2008 12:15 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: Newbie Intro and Questions




i have read many accounts that state evp sessions work better when you are
clear and focused. ( meditative)  I dont think it matters who you ask for-
its your preferences, ( in my opinion)- if you want to talk to a departed
loved one, it is fine to ask for them, but if they dont show up right away
dont be discouraged. Also, in my own personal experience, If you ask for
&#39;just anybody&#39;  then that is exactly who youll get! ( lol)





 Also, on a more personal and less itc note-

 sorry to the group that i havent been posting. I am at the start of a big
family move and we dont even have a new place to go yet- so the stress is at
all-time high levels....

( we are finally giving up as the drug lords in the upstairs half of our
house have ruined this home for us.)



Also- I am feeling a bit of a loss here... even tho it is partially (if not
all) selfish.

Monique ( one of my long-time spirit frineds) to my understanding has moved
on and gone to the light. Although this is excellent news for Monique, I DO
feel the lack of her presence around me, as she had been here nearly 17
years ( at least thats what she told me)

Anyway.... It feels like i lost a dear friend.... 

She was quite an excellent chatter and never even needed a riado or manual
sweep to leave clear evps for me. I hate to say it but i was sorry to see
her go.

 ( i know, selfish me )

anyways- i am keeping tabs on all your posts, glad to see the new members,
and as soon as i get my family into a new home i will get back into the
research that i love so dearly.

My apologies for not participating in the research at this time.

Charm





--- On Thu, 6/26/08, earthangel5998 &lt;harris5998@...&gt; wrote:

From: earthangel5998 &lt;harris5998@...&gt;
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: Newbie Intro and Questions
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Received: Thursday, June 26, 2008, 8:55 AM

Also...

Is there any way to &quot;prepare&quot; for recording like light a candle, 
meditate, etc? I am thinking maybe when I start sessions I can light a 
candle and when I end them I can blow the candle out kind of like a 
signal.

My grandfather- in-law and my father-in-law have both passed, should I 
try and ask for them by name or should I ask for anyone available? 

Sorry for the questions, I&#39;ve never done this before! 

Thanks! 
Angela 



